right off the bike.

09:07.160 --> 09:09.170
MARION:
Oh, my goodness!

09:09.170 --> 09:12.750
Yeah, it makes it a little
rough on the curves.

09:12.750 --> 09:15.250
Well, how did you get here?

09:15.250 --> 09:19.260
Well, I pushed
my bike 12 miles.

09:19.260 --> 09:22.260
The last three
on my knees.

09:22.760 --> 09:24.400
I can't walk
one more step.

09:24.400 --> 09:27.980
No. Well, it's all right.
Joanie will understand.

09:27.980 --> 09:29.490
Yeah, sure.

09:29.490 --> 09:30.490
There'll be
other marathons.

09:30.490 --> 09:31.990
She can enter next year.

09:31.990 --> 09:34.990
Oh, Fonzie, I'm
so glad you...

09:34.990 --> 09:35.990
Well, what happened?

09:36.490 --> 09:37.490
You're not even ready.

09:37.490 --> 09:38.950
Yeah, look,
Shortcake,

09:38.950 --> 09:40.530
I was coming
around this turn...

09:40.530 --> 09:42.250
You're not going
to the dance?

09:42.250 --> 09:44.330
HOWARD:
Well, sweetheart,
he tried to...

09:44.330 --> 09:47.340
No, no, no, whoa,
whoa, whoa...

09:47.340 --> 09:49.340
whoa...

09:49.340 --> 09:52.340
Would I give up
a date with a chick

09:52.340 --> 09:54.130
that is cuter than
a button, huh?

09:54.130 --> 09:56.210
No.

09:56.710 --> 09:58.210
I'll take a freshen-up shower,

09:58.210 --> 10:01.720
put on my dancing moccasins,
and I'll be fit as a fiddle.

10:03.270 --> 10:05.860
I saw it,  I saw it.
I'm in control.

10:05.860 --> 10:09.360
♪ Zippity do-dah,
zippity eh... ♪

10:09.360 --> 10:10.860
(groans)

10:15.560 --> 10:17.070
Is he all right?

10:17.070 --> 10:19.570
Oh, he's fit
as a fiddle,

10:19.570 --> 10:22.570
and he's a little
zippity do-dah, too.

10:22.570 --> 10:26.790
POTSIE:
♪ Venus, Goddess of love
that you are ♪

10:26.790 --> 10:31.250
♪ Surely the things I ask ♪

10:31.250 --> 10:34.330
♪ Won't be too great a task ♪

10:36.220 --> 10:38.550
♪ Venus, if you do ♪

10:38.550 --> 10:42.310
♪ I promise
that I always will be true ♪

10:42.310 --> 10:45.060
♪ I'll give her all the love
I have to give ♪

10:45.060 --> 10:48.650
