11:13.620 --> 11:17.210
Yowza, yowza, yowza,
that was Potsie Webber.

11:17.210 --> 11:20.380
Now everybody keep dancing, as
we approach the seven-hour mark.

11:20.380 --> 11:22.630
RICHIE:
Seven full...
Uh-oh, uh-oh.

11:22.630 --> 11:25.100
There's another couple
out of the marathon.

11:25.100 --> 11:29.190
Our judges Howard and Marion
Cunningham will assist them off.

11:29.190 --> 11:31.690
Who knows?

11:31.690 --> 11:35.030
Who will be the last couple
still dancing?

11:35.030 --> 11:36.650
Who can answer this question?

11:36.650 --> 11:39.230
Folks, we have more fish.

11:39.230 --> 11:40.730
Plenty of fish.

11:40.730 --> 11:42.400
Right, Al.

11:42.400 --> 11:46.240
RICHIE:
Who will be able to stand
the grueling, painful hours,

11:46.240 --> 11:50.330
and win for themselves
this wonderful trophy

11:50.330 --> 11:54.880
donated by Crepnicks
Foot Pad Company?

11:54.880 --> 11:57.720
Hey, Red, I'm growing tired
from listening to your voice.

11:57.720 --> 12:00.250
Uh, right, Bubba.

12:00.250 --> 12:02.340
Getting ready to
give up, Joanie?

12:02.340 --> 12:05.890
Let me tell you
something, little girl.

12:05.890 --> 12:08.480
This lady just asked me
to take her roller-skating

12:08.480 --> 12:11.400
when we win this
marathon, and we will.

12:11.400 --> 12:14.980
So I see we got a little
competition this year, huh?

12:14.980 --> 12:15.900
Very little.

12:17.320 --> 12:19.320
Do you know what
I think is terrific?

12:19.320 --> 12:21.110
That an elephant
learned how to talk.

12:28.660 --> 12:31.170
Well, then maybe you'd like
to make a little wager, huh?

12:31.170 --> 12:33.620
Say five bucks,
ducktail?

12:33.620 --> 12:37.670
Oh, no, come on, let's make it
ten, you creep.

12:37.670 --> 12:39.840
And, oh, oh, oh,

12:39.840 --> 12:41.930
just so that you
don't get confused,

12:41.930 --> 12:45.430
that's one dollar
for every finger on both hands,

12:45.430 --> 12:47.380
Bubble Brain.

12:47.380 --> 12:48.470
You're on!

12:48.470 --> 12:50.050
I want a challenge dance!

12:50.050 --> 12:52.640
Yowza, yowza, yowza.

12:52.640 --> 12:54.640
We got the first challenge dance
of the evening.

12:54.640 --> 12:57.640
Jill picks the dance and
challenges the other contestants

12:57.640 --> 13:00.150
to keep up or get disqualified.

13:00.150 --> 13:01.950
Name your dance, Jill.

13:01.950 --> 13:03.980
The jitterbug!

13:03.980 --> 13:07.070
RICHIE:
Oh, a killer,
a real killer dance.

13:07.070 --> 13:08.570
I'm glad
we only have to play.

13:08.570 --> 13:10.070
Let's hit it, boys.

13:10.070 --> 13:11.540
