when we start the next number.

14:33.070 --> 14:35.660
I feel great,
don't you, Fonz?

14:35.660 --> 14:37.160
Superb.

14:37.160 --> 14:39.660
Well, I'm gonna
go get a drink.

14:39.660 --> 14:41.580
Just rest a minute, okay?

14:43.500 --> 14:45.670
Hey, Fonz, you're
doing great. Fonz?

14:45.670 --> 14:47.250
Fonz!
Yeah?

14:47.250 --> 14:49.310
Oh, good.
There's only
six couples left.

14:49.310 --> 14:51.390
(wearily):
Oh, that's terrific.
Cunningham?

14:51.390 --> 14:52.390
Hmm?

14:52.390 --> 14:55.480
What are those two words
you start every sentence with?

14:55.480 --> 14:57.850
Yowza, yow...

14:57.850 --> 15:02.150
You're giving me a headache!

15:02.150 --> 15:04.240
Oh, I'm sorry about that.

15:04.240 --> 15:05.240
That's all right.

15:05.240 --> 15:07.740
Listen, why don't
you just tell Joanie

15:07.740 --> 15:09.530
about having to push
your bike all the way?

15:09.530 --> 15:11.110
She'll understand that.

15:11.110 --> 15:12.110
Hey, are you kidding me?

15:12.110 --> 15:15.110
This marathon means
so much to her, huh?

15:15.110 --> 15:17.120
I can make it.
I'm making it.

15:17.120 --> 15:18.870
(bell clangs twice)

15:18.870 --> 15:20.450
All right, Fonz,
good luck.

15:20.950 --> 15:22.840
And you're
looking terrific.

15:24.760 --> 15:27.180
RALPH:
Hey, Rich,
I can't sing anymore.

15:27.180 --> 15:29.210
I've sung the whole Top 40
and three hymns.

15:29.210 --> 15:31.260
Oh. Okay, you'd better
sing one, Ralph.

15:31.260 --> 15:32.260
I'll play the piano.

15:32.260 --> 15:33.770
Okay.

15:33.770 --> 15:37.300
Yowza, yowza.

15:37.300 --> 15:39.390
I mean, yes, sir.

15:39.390 --> 15:41.860
RICHIE:
It's time to end
the two-minute break.

15:41.860 --> 15:44.440
All contestants out
on the floor.

15:44.440 --> 15:46.610
We know how much
you love to do the twist.

15:46.610 --> 15:48.200
So, for our next number,
we're gonna...

15:48.200 --> 15:49.200
Cunningham?

15:49.700 --> 15:52.200
I think it's about time
that we do a waltz.

15:52.200 --> 15:53.650
A waltz?

15:53.650 --> 15:55.740
Oh, come on, Rich,
I don't want to do...

15:55.740 --> 16:04.080
♪ Oh, how we danced
on the night we were wed ♪

16:04.080 --> 16:15.010
♪ We vowed our true love,
though a word wasn't said ♪

16:15.010 --> 16:20.600
♪ The world was in bloom ♪

16:20.600 --> 16:26.400
♪ There were stars in the sky ♪

16:26.400 --> 16:36.610
♪ Except for the few that
were there in your eyes ♪

16:36.610 --> 16:41.700
♪ Dearly I held you close
in my arms ♪

16:41.700 --> 16:46.760
♪ Angels were singing a hymn
to your charms ♪

16:46.760 --> 16:54.380
♪ Two hearts gently beating
and murmuring low ♪

16:56.770 --> 17:11.980
♪ My darling, I love you so. ♪

17:11.980 --> 17:14.569
(song ends)

17:20.569 --> 17:21.910
Getting tired, Fonzie?

17:21.910 --> 17:23.490
JILL:
You can stop.

17:23.490 --> 17:24.990
Let me tell
you something.

17:24.990 --> 17:27.000
Even if I wanted
to stop, I can't.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.500
This body don't quit.
Huh.

17:30.500 --> 17:33.000
Well, then, maybe you'd like
to up our little bet.

17:33.000 --> 17:35.500
Up it where?

17:39.430 --> 17:40.510
Forget money.

17:40.510 --> 17:43.310
If we win, you get a crewcut.

17:43.310 --> 17:44.900
(Bubba cackling)

17:44.900 --> 17:46.230
Crewcut?
Let me tell you...

17:46.230 --> 17:47.320
(clucking)

17:47.320 --> 17:48.320
Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, whoa!

17:48.320 --> 17:49.320
Keep dancing.

17:49.320 --> 17:50.820
Yeah, you're right.
You're right.

17:50.820 --> 17:52.910
All right, all right,
I'm dancing, I'm dancing.

17:52.910 --> 17:55.990
Listen, if we lose, I'll get
a crewcut, but we won't, see?

17:55.990 --> 17:58.990
And when we win, then Miss
Cunningham here becomes

17:58.990 --> 18:01.500
a cheerleader like she should
have been in the first place.

18:01.500 --> 18:02.410
It's a bet.

18:02.410 --> 18:04.000
(falsetto):
It's a bet.

18:08.000 --> 18:10.510
Thanks, Fonz.
You're the greatest.

18:10.510 --> 18:12.510
Heyyy...

18:12.510 --> 18:15.010
Hold me up, will you?
Hold me up.

18:15.010 --> 18:17.510
Okay. Listen, listen.
if you have to get a crewcut,

18:17.510 --> 18:19.520
I'll knit you a cap.

18:19.520 --> 18:22.020
You'll knit me
a Spanish accent

18:22.020 --> 18:24.020
'cause I'm going
to Peru!

18:27.110 --> 18:28.640
(upbeat music playing)

18:36.060 --> 18:36.820
Fish...

18:40.820 --> 18:42.200
Yowza, yowza...

18:47.490 --> 18:48.790
(bell clangs)

18:50.300 --> 18:53.080
(wearily):
Yowza, yowza, yowza.

18:53.080 --> 18:56.670
RICHIE:
Here we are
in the 14th hour.

18:56.670 --> 18:59.170
There are still
three couples dancing.

19:01.670 --> 19:04.180
There are still
two couples dancing.

19:12.320 --> 19:15.900
We're dedicating this next
cha-cha challenge

19:15.900 --> 19:22.610
to those stubborn,
wonderful, rotten,
dancing fools.

19:23.110 --> 19:25.610
I can't sing
anymore, Rich.

19:25.610 --> 19:26.620
Me, neither.

19:26.620 --> 19:28.200
(drum solo)

19:31.670 --> 19:33.260
Show-off.

19:33.260 --> 19:35.260
Where do girls get
all that energy?

19:35.260 --> 19:36.260
I don't know.

19:36.260 --> 19:39.760
I hear girls have
extra-large adrenaline glands.

19:39.760 --> 19:40.760
You have to hear that?

19:40.760 --> 19:43.930
You couldn't see
for yourself?

19:43.930 --> 19:45.020
RICHIE:
We're gonna take
a two-minute break now.

19:45.020 --> 19:46.390
Let's take a break.

19:46.390 --> 19:46.970
(bell clangs)

19:49.470 --> 19:53.360
Oh, Fonz, no, don't lie down;
it'll be harder to get up.

19:53.360 --> 19:55.890
Don't you ever
get tired?

19:55.890 --> 19:58.480
JOANIE: No, it's
not a school night.

19:58.480 --> 19:59.450
MARION:
Arthur,

19:59.450 --> 20:00.530
are you all right, dear?

20:00.530 --> 20:06.070
Hey, it's like taking candy
from a baby, Mrs. Whoever.

20:06.070 --> 20:07.660
Howard...

20:07.660 --> 20:08.660
Huh?

20:08.660 --> 20:10.160
Arthur, he's had
too much.

20:10.160 --> 20:11.660
You've got
to disqualify him.

20:11.660 --> 20:13.660
No, I, I'm not going
to do that, Marion,

20:13.660 --> 20:15.160
but I'll talk to Joanie.

20:15.160 --> 20:17.670
It's better for her
if she makes the decision.

20:17.670 --> 20:18.670
Now, don't worry
about it.

20:18.670 --> 20:21.670
She's a sweet and
sympathetic girl.

20:21.670 --> 20:24.140
What do you mean,
you want to quit?!

20:24.140 --> 20:25.220
You can't quit!

20:25.220 --> 20:27.140
You're all talk,
no action!

20:34.820 --> 20:35.820
It worked!

20:35.820 --> 20:37.820
You're standing up, Fonz.
I knew you could do it.

20:37.820 --> 20:41.820
Hey, that was a trick?

20:41.820 --> 20:46.110
That was a good one,
Shortcake.

20:46.110 --> 20:48.200
Joanie, come here.
I gotta talk to you.

20:48.200 --> 20:49.700
Oh, I got Fonzie
going again.

20:49.700 --> 20:51.200
Boy, he tires easy.

20:51.200 --> 20:52.700
Yeah, but there's
a reason for it.

20:52.700 --> 20:54.200
Now, enough is enough.

20:54.200 --> 20:55.620
Oh, but I feel great!

20:55.620 --> 21:00.180
Joanie, it is not you!
Would you look at Fonzie?

21:01.680 --> 21:03.850
He's fine.
I keep tricking him.

21:03.850 --> 21:05.510
(bell clangs)

21:05.510 --> 21:06.600
Oh, gotta go, Dad.

21:06.600 --> 21:07.600
Wait a minute.

21:07.600 --> 21:10.350
Now, Fonzie didn't want you
to know this,

21:10.350 --> 21:13.940
but he pushed
his motorcycle 12 miles

21:13.940 --> 21:16.020
just to get
to this dance on time,

21:16.020 --> 21:17.610
for you.

21:17.610 --> 21:20.060
Now, do you still want
to go on tricking him?

21:26.540 --> 21:28.490
(bell clangs twice)

21:31.370 --> 21:33.960
I'm up, right?

21:33.960 --> 21:36.080
I'm up. My feet
are moving like a bandit.

21:36.080 --> 21:38.250
You're in la-la land, Fonz.

21:38.250 --> 21:39.830
Oh, yeah?

21:39.830 --> 21:43.590
Let me tell you something, it's
a lot of fun in la-la land.

21:43.590 --> 21:45.170
It might not look it,

21:45.170 --> 21:49.170
but inside,
I'm doing the mambo.

21:49.170 --> 21:51.180
Oh, Fonz,
the dance is over.

21:51.180 --> 21:52.680
Did we win, huh?
We won, huh?

21:52.680 --> 21:54.230
Hey, we won.

21:54.230 --> 21:56.820
Whoa, I knew we could make it.

21:56.820 --> 21:57.980
That's it.

21:57.980 --> 21:59.570
He really wanted
to go on.

21:59.570 --> 22:01.070
It's me, I quit.

22:01.070 --> 22:04.570
That's it! Fonzie's
finished. We win!

22:04.570 --> 22:07.330
Hey, Fonz, I know a barber
who gives great crewcuts!

22:07.330 --> 22:08.780
Crewcut!

22:12.330 --> 22:14.330
Crewcut?

22:14.330 --> 22:17.920
Hey, you're talking
about my hair here.

22:17.920 --> 22:18.920
Let me tell you something.

22:19.420 --> 22:21.260
I have a challenge dance
request.

22:21.260 --> 22:22.340
No.

22:22.840 --> 22:24.840
RICHIE:
Yowza, yowza...

22:24.840 --> 22:26.930
No yowza, just a challenge.

22:26.930 --> 22:29.010
This challenge dance
is called...

22:29.510 --> 22:30.850
(falsetto):
the kazatski!

22:33.220 --> 22:34.300
RICHIE:
We'll fake it.

22:34.300 --> 22:38.520
Yeah, one, two,
one, two, three!

22:38.520 --> 22:40.610
("Hava Nagila" playing)

22:49.200 --> 22:51.200
(rhythmic handclaps)

23:14.680 --> 23:15.680
Wow!

23:15.680 --> 23:17.180
(applause)

23:17.180 --> 23:19.180
(song ends, cheering)

23:20.650 --> 23:26.070
The winners are
Cunningham and Fonzarelli!

23:35.500 --> 23:39.030
I would just like to
thank someone, uh, here tonight

23:39.030 --> 23:42.450
without whom this whole thing
would not have been possible.

23:42.450 --> 23:45.540
Of course, I am
talking about myself.

23:46.790 --> 23:48.290
(applause)

23:48.290 --> 23:52.380
Also, uh, thanks very
much for my foot. Hmm.

23:52.380 --> 23:55.380
I would also like to say
that Joanie Cunningham,

23:55.380 --> 23:57.890
our newest pom-pom girl
at Jefferson High School

23:57.890 --> 23:58.890
is not bad, either.

23:59.390 --> 24:00.390
Thanks, Fonz.

24:00.390 --> 24:02.140
(applause)

24:02.140 --> 24:04.230
Don't tell Mom we lost.

24:04.230 --> 24:05.560
Oh, Bubba.

24:06.900 --> 24:08.360
FONZIE:
Girls?

24:11.900 --> 24:14.570
Home, James. Heyyy...

24:25.750 --> 24:27.330
You know something, Joanie?

24:27.330 --> 24:29.500
You were fantastic.

24:29.500 --> 24:31.090
(gasps)

24:31.090 --> 24:32.590
You kissed me!

24:32.590 --> 24:35.010
Oh, well, it-it's late.
I lost my head.

24:44.150 --> 24:45.730
Did you see that?

24:45.730 --> 24:48.240
She kissed her brother.

24:48.240 --> 24:50.240
It's been a day
of miracles.

24:50.240 --> 24:51.440
Yeah.

24:51.440 --> 24:52.520
Can I walk you home?

24:52.520 --> 24:54.530
Sure you can walk
me home, Jimmy.

24:54.530 --> 24:57.530
♪ These happy days are yours
and mine, Happy Days. ♪

25:01.030 --> 25:03.030
(rhythmic handclaps)

25:03.030 --> 25:05.040
♪ Good-bye gray sky,
hello, blue ♪

25:05.040 --> 25:08.090
♪ There's nothing can hold me
when I hold you ♪

25:08.090 --> 25:10.090
♪ It feels so right,
it can't be wrong ♪

25:10.090 --> 25:13.210
♪ Rockin' and rollin'
all week long ♪

25:13.210 --> 25:15.800
♪ These days are ours ♪

25:18.300 --> 25:20.800
♪ These days are ours ♪

25:20.800 --> 25:22.300
♪ Share them with me ♪

25:23.810 --> 25:34.520
♪ These happy days
are yours and mine ♪

